00:30:28.140 --> 00:30:29.810
AUDIENCE: Thanks
so much for coming.

00:30:29.810 --> 00:30:32.380
So I have kind of an unrelated
question to your book,

00:30:32.380 --> 00:30:34.480
but I know you mentioned
right at the get

00:30:34.480 --> 00:30:36.100
go, which really
caught my attention,

00:30:36.100 --> 00:30:38.027
that you've been
married for 38--

00:30:38.027 --> 00:30:40.110
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: It
will be 38 years this fall.

00:30:40.110 --> 00:30:40.930
AUDIENCE: 38 years.

00:30:40.930 --> 00:30:45.010
Can you just describe how did
you make that work in a culture

00:30:45.010 --> 00:30:46.510
that we live in that's just--

00:30:46.510 --> 00:30:49.900
I think the statistics
are showing at least 50%

00:30:49.900 --> 00:30:51.820
divorce rate in our country.

00:30:51.820 --> 00:30:53.530
I could be a little off on that.

00:30:53.530 --> 00:30:55.810
But could you just
talk about that?

00:30:55.810 --> 00:30:58.150
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Yeah.

00:30:58.150 --> 00:31:03.550
That is not an easy
short answer response.

00:31:03.550 --> 00:31:07.000
So one, I married
the wrath of God.

00:31:14.290 --> 00:31:16.990
I now believe the wrath
of God is the love of God.

00:31:16.990 --> 00:31:20.620
But you've got to understand,
kim is from North Dakota.

00:31:20.620 --> 00:31:23.770
She was born in
Minot, and her family

00:31:23.770 --> 00:31:25.870
migrated west-- big family.

00:31:25.870 --> 00:31:28.240
She has five sisters
and two brothers.

00:31:28.240 --> 00:31:32.040
Her and her five sisters
are called "the force,"

00:31:32.040 --> 00:31:34.990
and may the force be with you.

00:31:34.990 --> 00:31:40.990
So these folks,
Minnesota, North Dakota--

00:31:40.990 --> 00:31:43.080
I mean, there is no
fifty shades of nothing.

00:31:43.080 --> 00:31:46.510
It's either this or that.

00:31:46.510 --> 00:31:48.160
But I grew up in a
religious family,

00:31:48.160 --> 00:31:50.770
so we hid everything,
lied about most stuff,

00:31:50.770 --> 00:31:54.220
had to have an Order of
Service when we got together.

00:31:54.220 --> 00:31:56.100
Her family is just out there.

00:31:56.100 --> 00:31:58.870
Me, I got all these
survival mechanisms

00:31:58.870 --> 00:32:02.500
from my abuse histories,
so I'm all hyper vigilant

00:32:02.500 --> 00:32:06.790
and know how to shade
the truth in 5,000 ways.

00:32:06.790 --> 00:32:12.610
And at the same time, I'm
desperate for some healing

00:32:12.610 --> 00:32:14.950
in my own heart.

00:32:14.950 --> 00:32:17.469
But I wanted God to heal me
without anybody else finding

00:32:17.469 --> 00:32:18.010
out about it.

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:30.660
And frankly, I didn't marry
Kim because I loved her.

00:32:30.660 --> 00:32:32.700
Because at that
point in my life,

00:32:32.700 --> 00:32:35.400
I didn't know how
to love anyone.

00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:38.940
I had no love for myself,
because I believed

00:32:38.940 --> 00:32:41.550
all the theology about
being a piece of crap

00:32:41.550 --> 00:32:45.165
that I grew up with and
about the nature of God

00:32:45.165 --> 00:32:46.830
as different than Jesus--

00:32:46.830 --> 00:32:50.040
all that kind of stuff.

00:32:50.040 --> 00:32:53.220
But it turns out I'm smart
and creative, which actually

00:32:53.220 --> 00:32:56.100
was an inhibitor to healing.

00:32:56.100 --> 00:32:57.480
It empowered me to hide.

00:33:00.030 --> 00:33:04.260
And so I hid.

00:33:04.260 --> 00:33:08.650
I married Kim because I thought
I got the nudge from God

00:33:08.650 --> 00:33:11.760
to do that.

00:33:11.760 --> 00:33:15.210
I'm forever grateful
because she saved my life.

00:33:18.340 --> 00:33:22.870
Now, at the point where all of
my facade, all of my hiddenness

00:33:22.870 --> 00:33:24.220
was exposed--

00:33:24.220 --> 00:33:27.400
and I now believe that
exposure is a gift,

00:33:27.400 --> 00:33:30.670
but it's a severe mercy--

00:33:30.670 --> 00:33:37.810
when that happened,
I blew it all up.

00:33:37.810 --> 00:33:40.060
I blew my whole world up.

00:33:40.060 --> 00:33:44.330
And that's what started my
11-year dismantling/rebuilding

00:33:44.330 --> 00:33:44.830
process.

00:33:49.210 --> 00:33:53.940
And it was the
intensity of Kim's fury

00:33:53.940 --> 00:33:58.260
that pushed me to deal with
all the darkness in my heart.

00:33:58.260 --> 00:34:01.750
And so how did we make it work?

00:34:01.750 --> 00:34:07.680
One is when it all blew
up, I hit the bottom enough

00:34:07.680 --> 00:34:10.670
to own what I'd done--

00:34:10.670 --> 00:34:11.435
no more secrets.

00:34:14.940 --> 00:34:19.429
So when I got to 50, which is
at the end of that 11 years--

00:34:19.429 --> 00:34:23.949
it was 38 to the
year I turned 50.

00:34:23.949 --> 00:34:26.440
When I got there, I
was finally at a place

00:34:26.440 --> 00:34:30.310
where no secrets, no addictions,
and I was the same person

00:34:30.310 --> 00:34:31.270
in every situation.

00:34:34.500 --> 00:34:39.400
And there was reconciliation
in the midst of all the damage.

00:34:39.400 --> 00:34:41.610
So what I say is
Kim saved my life

00:34:41.610 --> 00:34:45.639
and paid a high price
for it, and she does not

00:34:45.639 --> 00:34:52.980
regret the high price but
it's totally not fair.

00:34:52.980 --> 00:34:54.610
It's grace.

00:34:54.610 --> 00:34:59.000
So part of it was
if I had deviated

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:02.540
from dealing with my
stuff when I got exposed,

00:35:02.540 --> 00:35:03.545
we wouldn't be together.

00:35:03.545 --> 00:35:04.670
It would not have happened.

00:35:07.220 --> 00:35:10.160
But her intensity is what
kept me dealing with it,

00:35:10.160 --> 00:35:13.970
at the same time
as my desperation.

00:35:13.970 --> 00:35:17.420
So I think that
one of the things

00:35:17.420 --> 00:35:19.670
I understand about
marriage-- and you remember

00:35:19.670 --> 00:35:23.370
when Jesus is talking
to the Pharisees

00:35:23.370 --> 00:35:25.120
because they're all
griping about the fact

00:35:25.120 --> 00:35:27.990
that his disciples are
violating Sabbath law?

00:35:27.990 --> 00:35:30.930
They're going, eating stuff
on the Sabbath, picking corn,

00:35:30.930 --> 00:35:32.380
working--

00:35:32.380 --> 00:35:34.990
all the rules, all
the religious rules.

00:35:34.990 --> 00:35:37.930
And Jesus says this
one line that just

00:35:37.930 --> 00:35:39.980
changes the entire universe.

00:35:39.980 --> 00:35:43.540
He says, don't you
realize that the Sabbath

00:35:43.540 --> 00:35:45.370
was made for the
human being, not

00:35:45.370 --> 00:35:48.130
the human being for Sabbath?

00:35:48.130 --> 00:35:53.300
Well, put in that
marriage, that marriage

00:35:53.300 --> 00:35:56.330
was made for the human
being, not the human being

00:35:56.330 --> 00:35:57.800
for marriage.

00:35:57.800 --> 00:36:00.170
And that begins to
change everything.

00:36:00.170 --> 00:36:03.770
That means that
marriage is defined

00:36:03.770 --> 00:36:06.860
as an outward expression of
the uniqueness of the two

00:36:06.860 --> 00:36:09.990
individuals involved in it.

00:36:09.990 --> 00:36:14.700
There is no external law of
the Sabbath, law of marriage,

00:36:14.700 --> 00:36:19.000
that defines what that's
supposed to look like for you.

00:36:19.000 --> 00:36:21.450
And that's what the Church,
frankly, has been good at.

00:36:21.450 --> 00:36:24.570
We come up with all kinds of
Sabbath laws or marriage laws

00:36:24.570 --> 00:36:26.190
or expectations.

00:36:26.190 --> 00:36:28.560
And as soon as something goes--

00:36:28.560 --> 00:36:32.670
suddenly the man who's supposed
to do this can't anymore--

00:36:32.670 --> 00:36:35.760
or whatever, whatever
the rules are.

00:36:35.760 --> 00:36:36.510
No.

00:36:36.510 --> 00:36:42.240
So part of it is to recognize
that marriage is something

00:36:42.240 --> 00:36:45.540
that you have to figure
out with the person

00:36:45.540 --> 00:36:47.100
that you are in a
relationship to,

00:36:47.100 --> 00:36:50.160
and it involves mystery
and a loss of control.

00:36:50.160 --> 00:36:52.340
Any relationship does.

00:36:52.340 --> 00:36:53.180
Ask any married man.

00:36:57.230 --> 00:37:00.630
And the thing about it is
that person is not static.

00:37:00.630 --> 00:37:02.000
They don't stay still.

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:03.440
They keep growing, too.

00:37:03.440 --> 00:37:06.090
So this mystery that
you then move into

00:37:06.090 --> 00:37:08.660
is an ever-expanding universe.

00:37:08.660 --> 00:37:10.880
And in the middle of that,
I was with Richard Rohr.

00:37:10.880 --> 00:37:12.338
I don't know if
you know who he is.

00:37:12.338 --> 00:37:14.330
So I did a conference
on the Trinity

00:37:14.330 --> 00:37:15.800
with him a couple of months ago.

00:37:15.800 --> 00:37:21.650
And so we were driving
along in his car.

00:37:21.650 --> 00:37:25.790
He's a Franciscan
celibate monk--

00:37:25.790 --> 00:37:29.780
vow of poverty, chastity,
and something else.

00:37:29.780 --> 00:37:33.030
And he says, Paul--

00:37:33.030 --> 00:37:35.360
and he's a Kansas City
farm boy who didn't ever

00:37:35.360 --> 00:37:38.699
expect to be involved
with writing the things

00:37:38.699 --> 00:37:39.240
that he does.

00:37:39.240 --> 00:37:41.390
And he says, you know what?

00:37:41.390 --> 00:37:44.840
This sounds weird coming from
a celibate Franciscan monk,

00:37:44.840 --> 00:37:49.010
but I'm convinced that marriage
is the greatest gift that God

00:37:49.010 --> 00:37:51.920
has given humanity,
as a crucible

00:37:51.920 --> 00:37:55.130
in which transformation
becomes a possibility.

00:37:58.770 --> 00:38:01.890
So part of the
integrity of marriage

00:38:01.890 --> 00:38:06.710
is that we commit ourselves
to the transformation

00:38:06.710 --> 00:38:09.950
of our own hearts and
recognize that this is a gift.

00:38:09.950 --> 00:38:13.010
So the difference is
that each person then

00:38:13.010 --> 00:38:16.070
becomes part of the
catalyst for change,

00:38:16.070 --> 00:38:19.220
but it's going to bring all
your crap to the surface.

00:38:19.220 --> 00:38:29.470
And we live in a world where
fear of missing out or 2.2

00:38:29.470 --> 00:38:33.220
becomes more attractive than
having to work through dealing

00:38:33.220 --> 00:38:35.800
with our own crap.

00:38:35.800 --> 00:38:40.240
And so that's part of the
problem that we're in.

00:38:40.240 --> 00:38:41.950
We don't know how
to make a commitment

00:38:41.950 --> 00:38:44.470
and stick with it when
it gets really hard,

00:38:44.470 --> 00:38:47.770
and it does get really hard.

00:38:47.770 --> 00:38:53.350
So those are parts of a
response to your question.

00:38:53.350 --> 00:38:56.290
I mean, I could spend the
whole day talking to you

00:38:56.290 --> 00:38:59.320
about some of that.

00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:04.082
And then at this point,
don't make choices based

00:39:04.082 --> 00:39:05.290
on what the culture is doing.

00:39:08.040 --> 00:39:11.950
If you work through the
stuff of your marriage,

00:39:11.950 --> 00:39:16.380
it will become attractive
to those who watch it.

00:39:16.380 --> 00:39:18.540
That's not the
reason why you do it.

00:39:18.540 --> 00:39:20.040
You do it because
you want to become

00:39:20.040 --> 00:39:21.300
an authentic human being.

00:39:21.300 --> 00:39:23.550
That's why you do it.

00:39:23.550 --> 00:39:29.340
And this is a gift, as severe
a mercy as it is sometimes.

00:39:29.340 --> 00:39:33.750
13 years after I
blew my world up--

00:39:33.750 --> 00:39:37.020
I got a one-sentence phone call
on January 4, '94, from Kim.

00:39:37.020 --> 00:39:39.540
And all she said was, I'm
waiting for you at your office

00:39:39.540 --> 00:39:41.420
and I know.

00:39:41.420 --> 00:39:44.110
And what she knew was I was in
a three-month affair with one

00:39:44.110 --> 00:39:47.680
of her best friends, and that
was after our sixth child had

00:39:47.680 --> 00:39:49.660
been born.

00:39:49.660 --> 00:39:52.850
So I mean, I blew up the world.

00:39:52.850 --> 00:39:57.776
I broke-- I broke the world.

00:39:57.776 --> 00:39:58.276
Yeah.

00:40:01.494 --> 00:40:03.910
And at that point, I had to
decide whether to kill myself.

00:40:03.910 --> 00:40:09.160
Suicide has always been
a relative, a companion,

00:40:09.160 --> 00:40:11.985
because it's the last way to
run away before you actually

00:40:11.985 --> 00:40:12.610
hit the bottom.

00:40:15.160 --> 00:40:17.310
Or face her.

00:40:17.310 --> 00:40:22.640
And I still don't know
how I made it across town.

00:40:25.280 --> 00:40:26.360
I mean, I went into--

00:40:26.360 --> 00:40:28.100
I pulled the Yellow
Pages off the shelf,

00:40:28.100 --> 00:40:34.026
and we can go into so many
mysterious graces that

00:40:34.026 --> 00:40:35.150
were in the middle of this.

00:40:35.150 --> 00:40:37.850
I pull the Yellow
Pages off the shelf

00:40:37.850 --> 00:40:41.750
and end up sitting in front of
a total stranger who becomes

00:40:41.750 --> 00:40:44.180
a friend and a therapist.

00:40:44.180 --> 00:40:45.290
And that was part of it.

00:40:45.290 --> 00:40:47.540
Kim didn't demand that.

00:40:47.540 --> 00:40:51.010
For the first time in
my life I needed help.

00:40:51.010 --> 00:40:53.980
I wish I had
acknowledged it before.

00:40:53.980 --> 00:40:58.500
But some of us are so broken,
we have to get caught.

00:40:58.500 --> 00:41:01.620
And 13 years later,
we're sitting in a group.

00:41:01.620 --> 00:41:04.830
Because we never made my
adultery the new secret.

00:41:04.830 --> 00:41:08.220
And we're sitting in a group of
friends, all who knew my story.

00:41:08.220 --> 00:41:11.370
And Kim says to them
in front of me--

00:41:11.370 --> 00:41:16.910
she says, you know, I never
thought I would ever say this.

00:41:16.910 --> 00:41:19.736
It was all worth it.

00:41:19.736 --> 00:41:22.850
And she's not
justifying adultery.

00:41:22.850 --> 00:41:27.300
She's not saying the means
justify the ends or the ends

00:41:27.300 --> 00:41:28.350
justify the means.

00:41:28.350 --> 00:41:33.517
She's saying, there's nothing so
broken that God can't heal it,

00:41:33.517 --> 00:41:35.100
or so lost that God
doesn't know where

00:41:35.100 --> 00:41:41.580
it is, or so dead that God
can't grow something in it.

00:41:41.580 --> 00:41:44.870
And she was saying,
he's worth it.

00:41:44.870 --> 00:41:47.050
AUDIENCE: What a lovely story.

00:41:47.050 --> 00:41:48.580
That was so great.

00:41:48.580 --> 00:41:51.250
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Well, you
asked the question, darling.

00:41:51.250 --> 00:41:53.860
But it's the way it is.

00:41:53.860 --> 00:41:57.310
So to be involved on this side,
in the ripple effect of all

00:41:57.310 --> 00:42:01.970
this, it's an incredible grace.

00:42:01.970 --> 00:42:03.959
I'm very grateful.

00:42:03.959 --> 00:42:04.500
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:42:04.500 --> 00:42:08.260
I recently read "Lies
We Believe About God."

00:42:08.260 --> 00:42:09.800
I felt like I was
having difficulty

00:42:09.800 --> 00:42:11.330
understanding your position.

00:42:11.330 --> 00:42:13.370
Because while you
include many proof texts

00:42:13.370 --> 00:42:16.760
for a universal
salvation of man,

00:42:16.760 --> 00:42:19.385
there was no address of the many
verses that suggest otherwise.

00:42:19.385 --> 00:42:20.884
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG:
Did you not read

00:42:20.884 --> 00:42:22.104
the [? catina ?] at the back?

00:42:22.104 --> 00:42:22.770
AUDIENCE: I did.

00:42:22.770 --> 00:42:27.450
Yeah, those all seemed to
be proof texts for, right?

00:42:27.450 --> 00:42:29.450
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Well,
they were just a list.

00:42:29.450 --> 00:42:30.630
AUDIENCE: Yeah, it was
just a list of verses,

00:42:30.630 --> 00:42:32.450
but I wanted to see
verses that seemed

00:42:32.450 --> 00:42:34.760
to suggest against the
universal salvation of man.

00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:37.560
I wanted to hear what you
had to say about those.

00:42:37.560 --> 00:42:39.200
I have one verse
I'd like to read--

00:42:39.200 --> 00:42:40.824
or, well, two verses
I'd like to read--

00:42:40.824 --> 00:42:43.820
and then I'd like to ask
a clarifying question.

00:42:43.820 --> 00:42:47.150
Revelation 20: 9-10 say,
"And they marched up

00:42:47.150 --> 00:42:48.950
over the broad
plain of the earth

00:42:48.950 --> 00:42:52.430
and surrounded the camp of the
saints and the beloved city,

00:42:52.430 --> 00:42:54.830
but fire came down from
heaven and consumed them.

00:42:54.830 --> 00:42:56.630
And the devil who
had deceived them

00:42:56.630 --> 00:42:59.420
was thrown into the
lake of fire and sulfur,

00:42:59.420 --> 00:43:01.310
where the beast and
the false prophet were.

00:43:01.310 --> 00:43:04.140
And they will be tormented day
and night, forever and ever."

00:43:04.140 --> 00:43:05.859
So the clarifying
question is, do you

00:43:05.859 --> 00:43:07.400
believe that, in
addition to mankind,

00:43:07.400 --> 00:43:10.760
that also the devils
are redeemed, forgiven,

00:43:10.760 --> 00:43:13.436
and spared eternal punishment?

00:43:17.330 --> 00:43:21.850
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Well,
you couched your question

00:43:21.850 --> 00:43:23.680
with an assumption that's false.

00:43:23.680 --> 00:43:24.970
AUDIENCE: OK, sure.

00:43:24.970 --> 00:43:27.220
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: So the
first part of your question

00:43:27.220 --> 00:43:28.764
was, do you also believe that?

00:43:28.764 --> 00:43:30.430
And then you made a
statement about what

00:43:30.430 --> 00:43:31.716
I believe about everybody.

00:43:31.716 --> 00:43:33.715
AUDIENCE: That's why it's
a clarifying question.

00:43:33.715 --> 00:43:34.275
Thanks.

00:43:34.275 --> 00:43:35.650
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG:
So let's talk

00:43:35.650 --> 00:43:38.110
about universal
salvation for a second.

00:43:38.110 --> 00:43:40.570
That's a very different
thing than the idea

00:43:40.570 --> 00:43:43.330
that everyone will ultimately
be reconciled back face

00:43:43.330 --> 00:43:45.550
to face with the Father,
Son, and Holy Spirit.

00:43:45.550 --> 00:43:47.070
Do you understand
the distinction?

00:43:47.070 --> 00:43:48.820
AUDIENCE: I do understand
the distinction,

00:43:48.820 --> 00:43:53.937
but I understood the
former from the book.

00:43:53.937 --> 00:43:55.020
But go ahead and continue.

00:43:55.020 --> 00:43:57.610
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: No, I went
to great pains to say, no,

00:43:57.610 --> 00:43:59.640
I don't know.

00:43:59.640 --> 00:44:03.410
Here's a question that
I'd like to ask back.

00:44:03.410 --> 00:44:08.220
If God, in God's wisdom and
counsel within the Father, Son,

00:44:08.220 --> 00:44:11.450
and Holy Spirit, from
prior to creation,

00:44:11.450 --> 00:44:15.170
knew how to win every
single part of creation

00:44:15.170 --> 00:44:20.312
back and redeem it, would
you be opposed to it?

00:44:20.312 --> 00:44:21.770
AUDIENCE: Would I
be opposed to it?

00:44:21.770 --> 00:44:22.880
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Yeah.

00:44:22.880 --> 00:44:25.992
AUDIENCE: I am for
whatever God is for.

00:44:25.992 --> 00:44:28.200
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: So you
wouldn't be opposed to it?

00:44:28.200 --> 00:44:30.722
AUDIENCE: I'd have to think
more about what you're saying.

00:44:30.722 --> 00:44:33.180
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Well, I'm
saying I'm not opposed to it.

00:44:33.180 --> 00:44:36.450
Actually, I hope that that's
true, but I don't know.

00:44:36.450 --> 00:44:40.860
So I'm not holding to a doctrine
of universal reconciliation.

00:44:40.860 --> 00:44:43.410
But universal salvation,
that goes all the way back

00:44:43.410 --> 00:44:46.980
to the early Church, as far
as saying that what Jesus did

00:44:46.980 --> 00:44:49.920
affected every
single human being

00:44:49.920 --> 00:44:54.810
on the planet who
would ever exist.

00:44:54.810 --> 00:44:56.820
He died once for all.

00:44:56.820 --> 00:44:59.460
This is a statement that is true
and worthy of full acceptance

00:44:59.460 --> 00:45:02.610
that Jesus Christ is the
savior of all mankind.

00:45:02.610 --> 00:45:05.130
If I be lifted up, I'll
drag all men to myself.

00:45:05.130 --> 00:45:07.530
That word is only used
for dragging the fish that

00:45:07.530 --> 00:45:11.490
were breaking the nets, Paul and
Silas in front of the council,

00:45:11.490 --> 00:45:12.780
and in that verse.

00:45:12.780 --> 00:45:19.290
So the majority statement
throughout Christian history

00:45:19.290 --> 00:45:25.360
has been that universal
salvation exists for everyone,

00:45:25.360 --> 00:45:26.430
and it was accomplished.

00:45:26.430 --> 00:45:28.610
It was finished in Christ.

00:45:28.610 --> 00:45:31.520
The question is, do
you want it or not?

00:45:31.520 --> 00:45:36.680
Because your choice continues
to matter in an ongoing sense.

00:45:36.680 --> 00:45:39.020
So relationship is
always contingent.

00:45:39.020 --> 00:45:44.485
Relationship is always about
your ability to choose.

00:45:44.485 --> 00:45:45.440
We have six children.

00:45:45.440 --> 00:45:48.240
If one of my children--

00:45:48.240 --> 00:45:51.060
say our oldest son, say Chad--

00:45:51.060 --> 00:45:53.430
decides that he never
wants to talk to me again,

00:45:53.430 --> 00:45:56.060
wants to change his name,
whatever, ontologically he's

00:45:56.060 --> 00:45:56.850
still my son.

00:45:56.850 --> 00:46:00.700
But it completely
affects the relationship

00:46:00.700 --> 00:46:01.990
in an ongoing sense.

00:46:01.990 --> 00:46:06.010
Because part of
relationship is that I

00:46:06.010 --> 00:46:08.590
respect the choices that he
makes as a human being to say

00:46:08.590 --> 00:46:10.150
no.

00:46:10.150 --> 00:46:12.630
Well, that impacts relationship.

00:46:12.630 --> 00:46:15.570
Does it ontologically
make him not my son?

00:46:15.570 --> 00:46:16.710
No.

00:46:16.710 --> 00:46:19.290
And we're saying--
and I say "we"--

00:46:21.910 --> 00:46:24.820
the tradition of the
Church historically

00:46:24.820 --> 00:46:27.730
is that ontologically,
our salvation

00:46:27.730 --> 00:46:31.630
is accomplished in Christ, yet
we still have to work it out.

00:46:31.630 --> 00:46:34.330
What he has already worked
in, we got to work it out.

00:46:34.330 --> 00:46:36.140
Our choices actually matter.

00:46:36.140 --> 00:46:37.630
You can participate or not.

00:46:37.630 --> 00:46:40.750
Potentially, you can
say no to this forever.

00:46:40.750 --> 00:46:44.400
But part of my belief
is, my opinion is,

00:46:44.400 --> 00:46:46.780
is that love will
never stop pursuing,

00:46:46.780 --> 00:46:49.330
and death is not
what defines things.

00:46:49.330 --> 00:46:52.360
It is God who is life
who defines everything.

00:46:52.360 --> 00:46:53.890
That's a whole
different question

00:46:53.890 --> 00:46:57.974
than the issue of looking at
Revelation, that whole passage.

00:46:57.974 --> 00:46:59.140
Are we dealing with symbols?

00:46:59.140 --> 00:47:00.340
What do those symbols mean?

00:47:00.340 --> 00:47:01.774
What's it talking about?

00:47:01.774 --> 00:47:03.940
AUDIENCE: I wasn't so much
asking about the passage,

00:47:03.940 --> 00:47:04.690
just reading it.

00:47:04.690 --> 00:47:07.960
And then this question
comes up of devils.

00:47:11.200 --> 00:47:13.060
You say in the book
that death does not

00:47:13.060 --> 00:47:14.426
stop someone's free will.

00:47:14.426 --> 00:47:15.800
They can continue
to choose that.

00:47:15.800 --> 00:47:16.841
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Yeah.

00:47:16.841 --> 00:47:19.750
The potential is that everything
is restored-- potentially,

00:47:19.750 --> 00:47:22.270
because it depends on
how you define fire.

00:47:22.270 --> 00:47:24.760
When I say I married the
wrath of God, which I believe

00:47:24.760 --> 00:47:27.520
is the love of God,
I'm making a statement

00:47:27.520 --> 00:47:29.470
about the nature of fire.

00:47:29.470 --> 00:47:32.890
And that's a huge conversation.

00:47:32.890 --> 00:47:37.150
If you want to explore it
more, because I don't want

00:47:37.150 --> 00:47:42.500
to get stuck in a
mind conversation,

00:47:42.500 --> 00:47:44.950
scriptural, proof
texting conversation

00:47:44.950 --> 00:47:47.500
at the moment, because we just
don't have the time for it--

00:47:47.500 --> 00:47:50.800
but read Brad Jersak's
"Her Gates Will Never Be

00:47:50.800 --> 00:47:53.650
Shut," which is a reference
to that very passage

00:47:53.650 --> 00:47:54.970
in Revelation.

00:47:54.970 --> 00:47:57.580
But it's one of the best
explorations about this.

00:47:57.580 --> 00:48:00.010
My opinion is that the fire--

00:48:00.010 --> 00:48:03.020
God is fire, and
I believe in fire.

00:48:03.020 --> 00:48:04.390
In fact, I count on it.

00:48:04.390 --> 00:48:07.540
Like George MacDonald says, "If
you trust the goodness of God,

00:48:07.540 --> 00:48:09.520
you will run to him with
your arms wide open,

00:48:09.520 --> 00:48:11.944
and you will say, please,
judge me to the core

00:48:11.944 --> 00:48:13.360
and burn out of
me everything that

00:48:13.360 --> 00:48:16.180
keeps me from being fully
human and fully alive."

00:48:16.180 --> 00:48:18.400
But I believe that the
furious fire of God

00:48:18.400 --> 00:48:21.250
is always for us,
not against us,

00:48:21.250 --> 00:48:25.750
but is always against everything
that is not of love's kind,

00:48:25.750 --> 00:48:28.720
that God will not stand
idly by while anything

00:48:28.720 --> 00:48:31.960
that is not of love's
kind remains unchallenged.

00:48:31.960 --> 00:48:35.980
So that's the statement that
I would categorically say.

00:48:35.980 --> 00:48:41.050
So again, for the sake of
time and this conversation,

00:48:41.050 --> 00:48:43.697
we can pick that up, but
check out Brad's book.

00:48:43.697 --> 00:48:44.530
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:48:44.530 --> 00:48:46.570
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Thank you.

00:48:46.570 --> 00:48:47.430
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:48:47.430 --> 00:48:48.820
Great to see you again, Paul.

00:48:48.820 --> 00:48:51.910
So during this
11-year process, what

00:48:51.910 --> 00:48:53.740
was the key moment
in there that led you

00:48:53.740 --> 00:48:57.550
to this new view of God,
to view God as relational,

00:48:57.550 --> 00:49:01.180
to view God as this community
of persons, Father, Son,

00:49:01.180 --> 00:49:02.050
and Spirit?

00:49:02.050 --> 00:49:02.880
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Yeah, the
key moment was getting caught.

00:49:02.880 --> 00:49:05.213
AUDIENCE: So many Christians
have no conception of that,

00:49:05.213 --> 00:49:09.340
so what triggered that?

00:49:09.340 --> 00:49:12.385
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG:
Well, that is a process.

00:49:15.250 --> 00:49:19.570
You have to have the lies
exposed that underlie, that

00:49:19.570 --> 00:49:23.720
bring the disconnect and the
incoherence to your life.

00:49:23.720 --> 00:49:26.950
And so it happened in
many, many different ways.

00:49:26.950 --> 00:49:31.180
It happened through opening
my world up to relationships,

00:49:31.180 --> 00:49:35.620
not just with Kim and our
kids but with friends.

00:49:35.620 --> 00:49:39.880
And it had to do with
beginning to question some

00:49:39.880 --> 00:49:43.476
of the fundamental tenets that
I grew up with-- the nature

00:49:43.476 --> 00:49:44.350
and character of God.

00:49:44.350 --> 00:49:46.000
Is God good all the time?

00:49:46.000 --> 00:49:47.979
Is this a love that is
for me or against me?

00:49:47.979 --> 00:49:50.020
Is there a difference in
the nature and character

00:49:50.020 --> 00:49:51.280
of the Father and the Son?

00:49:51.280 --> 00:49:53.550
What do I do with
some of the atonement

00:49:53.550 --> 00:49:55.480
there is that we're
not taught as theories

00:49:55.480 --> 00:49:57.130
when I was growing up?

00:49:57.130 --> 00:50:00.580
So that reinforced
this separation

00:50:00.580 --> 00:50:05.184
and fear construct,
all of those things.

00:50:05.184 --> 00:50:06.850
And then beginning
to realize that there

00:50:06.850 --> 00:50:10.900
is nothing deeper as I
journeyed into the questions

00:50:10.900 --> 00:50:14.590
about the Trinity, which
I had been since I was 18.

00:50:14.590 --> 00:50:17.800
I mean, my journey
started with questions.

00:50:17.800 --> 00:50:19.660
In fact, my journey
into the Trinity

00:50:19.660 --> 00:50:23.300
came from the issue of women,
because most of the damage

00:50:23.300 --> 00:50:24.806
in my life came from men.

00:50:24.806 --> 00:50:26.180
And as I looked
around the world,

00:50:26.180 --> 00:50:28.576
most of the damage in
the world comes from men.

00:50:28.576 --> 00:50:30.950
And as I looked in scripture,
through one man sin entered

00:50:30.950 --> 00:50:33.290
the world, all the brokenness.

00:50:33.290 --> 00:50:36.620
And so I'm going, if men are so
much more messed up than women,

00:50:36.620 --> 00:50:39.080
how come they're in charge--

00:50:39.080 --> 00:50:43.070
because of my evangelical,
hierarchical fundamentalism.

00:50:43.070 --> 00:50:45.252
That drove me into
the Trinity, going,

00:50:45.252 --> 00:50:47.085
if there's hierarchy
in human relationships,

00:50:47.085 --> 00:50:49.910
there's got to be a
hierarchy in the Trinity.

00:50:49.910 --> 00:50:51.410
And if you've done
any study at all,

00:50:51.410 --> 00:50:54.810
you know that any version
of hierarchy in the Trinity

00:50:54.810 --> 00:50:57.330
has been declared heresy
by every single Christian

00:50:57.330 --> 00:51:01.217
tradition historically,
without exception.

00:51:01.217 --> 00:51:03.300
The eternal subordination
of the Son or the Father

00:51:03.300 --> 00:51:05.070
is heresy, et cetera.

00:51:05.070 --> 00:51:08.490
So if there is no hierarchy
within that circle

00:51:08.490 --> 00:51:11.130
of relationship and
we're created in it,

00:51:11.130 --> 00:51:12.870
that begins to
change everything.

00:51:12.870 --> 00:51:15.870
So not only was it relational
stuff that was happening.

00:51:15.870 --> 00:51:20.250
It was also the reading of some
of the early Church fathers,

00:51:20.250 --> 00:51:23.160
some of the theologians
through the centuries,

00:51:23.160 --> 00:51:25.920
as well as the impact
of art, the impact

00:51:25.920 --> 00:51:27.570
of music, the impact
of these things

00:51:27.570 --> 00:51:32.690
that penetrated past all my
ways of hiding inside my head.

00:51:32.690 --> 00:51:37.870
Then having children
had a huge impact

00:51:37.870 --> 00:51:40.030
on moving me out of my head.

00:51:40.030 --> 00:51:42.340
So there's all these
incremental little things.

00:51:42.340 --> 00:51:44.560
During that 11
years, a lot of it

00:51:44.560 --> 00:51:46.420
was just in
conversation, whether it

00:51:46.420 --> 00:51:49.420
was dealing with my own
stuff therapeutically

00:51:49.420 --> 00:51:54.190
or beginning to realize how
relationships had damaged me

00:51:54.190 --> 00:51:56.860
and how it was relationships
that were bringing me back

00:51:56.860 --> 00:51:59.770
to wholeness and
then driving that

00:51:59.770 --> 00:52:03.280
into my understanding of the
relationship of the Father,

00:52:03.280 --> 00:52:04.255
Son, and Holy Spirit.

00:52:04.255 --> 00:52:06.682
The Trinity is very
central for me,

00:52:06.682 --> 00:52:08.140
because I don't
think apart from it

00:52:08.140 --> 00:52:11.470
you have a basis anywhere
for love and relationship.

00:52:11.470 --> 00:52:16.137
There has to be other-centered
self-givingness to an other,

00:52:16.137 --> 00:52:17.470
and that has to be always there.

00:52:17.470 --> 00:52:20.056
So that all just began to
expand and trickle out.

00:52:20.056 --> 00:52:21.764
AUDIENCE: One thing
is, the subordination

00:52:21.764 --> 00:52:23.347
of the Son to the
Father is back again

00:52:23.347 --> 00:52:25.690
as a major topic of
discussion right now.

00:52:25.690 --> 00:52:28.170
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: I know,
but we tend to do that.

00:52:28.170 --> 00:52:30.704
Hard to leave old habits.

00:52:30.704 --> 00:52:32.995
SPEAKER 1: Yeah, and I actually
had a question for you.

00:52:32.995 --> 00:52:35.536
You mentioned "The Shack" did
everything you wanted it to do.

00:52:35.536 --> 00:52:38.170
It went out to those
dozen people there.

00:52:38.170 --> 00:52:41.774
But now that it has gone out
to millions around the world,

00:52:41.774 --> 00:52:43.690
is there anything you
would want to change now

00:52:43.690 --> 00:52:45.112
that it is larger?

00:52:45.112 --> 00:52:46.070
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: No.

00:52:46.070 --> 00:52:50.740
There is a really
glaring mistake in it,

00:52:50.740 --> 00:52:54.250
but I don't want to change it
because I like talking about it

00:52:54.250 --> 00:52:58.210
as a mistake so that people
don't make something out of it

00:52:58.210 --> 00:53:00.137
that it isn't.

00:53:00.137 --> 00:53:02.470
There is a scene when McKenzie
goes back into the shack.

00:53:02.470 --> 00:53:05.410
And it's not in the movie, but
I talked to them about this.

00:53:05.410 --> 00:53:07.750
And they did shoot it this
way, but it didn't make it

00:53:07.750 --> 00:53:10.087
through the editing process.

00:53:10.087 --> 00:53:11.920
When Mackenzie goes
back into the shack that

00:53:11.920 --> 00:53:16.000
has been transformed,
which is the presence

00:53:16.000 --> 00:53:18.220
of God declaring
the truth of who

00:53:18.220 --> 00:53:21.940
he is, even if he
can't recognize it

00:53:21.940 --> 00:53:25.480
except for this broken down
place where he's stuck.

00:53:25.480 --> 00:53:28.460
He goes in and he looks to where
Missy's blood stain should be,

00:53:28.460 --> 00:53:30.130
and it's gone.

00:53:30.130 --> 00:53:34.180
I think that's a mistake,
that it should still be there.

00:53:34.180 --> 00:53:40.750
Now, just because you work
through the arduous nature

00:53:40.750 --> 00:53:43.090
of your own damage doesn't
mean that the evidence of it

00:53:43.090 --> 00:53:44.770
just disappears.

00:53:44.770 --> 00:53:46.910
There are still nail scars.

00:53:46.910 --> 00:53:49.120
And one of the beautiful
things in the movie

00:53:49.120 --> 00:53:51.290
is that those nail scars exist.

00:53:51.290 --> 00:53:53.110
They're on Papa, which
is like the book,

00:53:53.110 --> 00:53:56.380
and same with Sarayu, the
Holy Spirit, and on Jesus.

00:53:56.380 --> 00:53:59.230
And that comes from,
where was God the Father?

00:53:59.230 --> 00:54:01.450
For God was in Christ
reconciling the world

00:54:01.450 --> 00:54:02.500
to himself.

00:54:02.500 --> 00:54:07.330
And that's a theme that we
could talk about theologically.

00:54:07.330 --> 00:54:13.120
But having the blood stain there
is a declaration of something

00:54:13.120 --> 00:54:15.040
that I think is
really significant,

00:54:15.040 --> 00:54:20.400
and that is, the
question that is

00:54:20.400 --> 00:54:26.190
behind my wrestling with
this mistake is that--

00:54:26.190 --> 00:54:29.090
who originates the cross?

00:54:29.090 --> 00:54:30.230
The scars are still there.

00:54:30.230 --> 00:54:32.090
Who originates the cross?

00:54:32.090 --> 00:54:34.820
And I don't think the
cross originates in God,

00:54:34.820 --> 00:54:37.400
because God is light and in God
there is no darkness at all.

00:54:37.400 --> 00:54:39.650
And there's nothing light
about a torture device

00:54:39.650 --> 00:54:40.940
called a cross.

00:54:40.940 --> 00:54:42.875
And historically, we
know who invented it

00:54:42.875 --> 00:54:44.000
and all this kind of stuff.

00:54:44.000 --> 00:54:47.330
But its only existence is
to keep a human being alive

00:54:47.330 --> 00:54:49.460
as long as possible and in
as much pain as possible

00:54:49.460 --> 00:54:51.980
and then forcibly extract
their breath from them.

00:54:51.980 --> 00:54:54.600
That's the purpose of it.

00:54:54.600 --> 00:55:00.950
So how does God then dismantle
this iconic statement

00:55:00.950 --> 00:55:02.840
of a fist in the face of God?

00:55:02.840 --> 00:55:05.780
Because it is the
symbol of iniquity,

00:55:05.780 --> 00:55:10.370
that we would do this to even a
human being, while God destroys

00:55:10.370 --> 00:55:12.470
its power by submitting to it--

00:55:12.470 --> 00:55:15.800
which is just beyond
our comprehension,

00:55:15.800 --> 00:55:18.950
that God comes and submits
to us as a baby who grows up

00:55:18.950 --> 00:55:20.900
and then climbs on
to our torture device

00:55:20.900 --> 00:55:23.120
in order to destroy its power.

00:55:23.120 --> 00:55:25.670
He destroys the power of
death that is represented

00:55:25.670 --> 00:55:27.380
by this torture device.

00:55:27.380 --> 00:55:28.790
But here's the beauty.

00:55:28.790 --> 00:55:31.280
He not only destroys
it by submitting to it,

00:55:31.280 --> 00:55:34.310
but transforms it into an icon
and a monument of grace that

00:55:34.310 --> 00:55:36.800
has become precious
to us, that we'll wear

00:55:36.800 --> 00:55:39.260
on our rings and our jewelry.

00:55:39.260 --> 00:55:41.180
Because he's changed that.

00:55:41.180 --> 00:55:43.430
That tells me that
there is no darkness

00:55:43.430 --> 00:55:45.740
that I can bring to the
table that God can't

00:55:45.740 --> 00:55:47.630
climb into the middle
of and transform

00:55:47.630 --> 00:55:50.890
into an icon and a
monument of grace.

00:55:50.890 --> 00:55:52.770
And so I can look
at my life and go,

00:55:52.770 --> 00:55:56.740
OK, I'm not alone, because I'm
created in the image of a God

00:55:56.740 --> 00:55:58.480
who has never been alone.

00:55:58.480 --> 00:56:01.850
And I'm created in the
middle of that relationship.

00:56:01.850 --> 00:56:05.090
And this God is with me
in order to co-create

00:56:05.090 --> 00:56:07.940
with my participation, because
God won't heal us apart

00:56:07.940 --> 00:56:12.140
from our participation,
something that is living.

00:56:12.140 --> 00:56:14.720
And He will transform
the mess that

00:56:14.720 --> 00:56:18.860
is my life into an icon
and a monument to grace.

00:56:18.860 --> 00:56:21.234
So that's one of those things.

00:56:21.234 --> 00:56:23.150
There are lots of things
that you could change

00:56:23.150 --> 00:56:27.234
that could be said better.

00:56:27.234 --> 00:56:28.400
SPEAKER 1: That's well done.

00:56:28.400 --> 00:56:30.230
So we have time for
one quick question.

00:56:30.230 --> 00:56:34.405
Is there anyone that has
a one-minute request?

00:56:38.200 --> 00:56:42.070
AUDIENCE: Can you tell us
about how Papa was inspired?

00:56:42.070 --> 00:56:44.360
WILLIAM PAUL YOUNG: Yeah, Papa.

00:56:44.360 --> 00:56:46.580
Papa God, large, black
African-American woman.

00:56:46.580 --> 00:56:49.250
And just so you know,
a lot of my people

00:56:49.250 --> 00:56:53.612
had a problem with
that, like my mom.

00:56:53.612 --> 00:56:55.820
My mom tried to read the
book, and the first time she

00:56:55.820 --> 00:56:57.361
tried to read it,
she closed the book

00:56:57.361 --> 00:56:59.500
when God the Father
came through the door

00:56:59.500 --> 00:57:02.120
as a large, black,
African-American woman.

00:57:02.120 --> 00:57:04.560
That's why Octavia
Spencer plays Papa.

00:57:07.265 --> 00:57:08.747
And she called my
sister and said,

00:57:08.747 --> 00:57:09.830
your brother is a heretic.

00:57:09.830 --> 00:57:11.990
So it's not like I
haven't heard it.

00:57:14.670 --> 00:57:20.220
God is traditionally-- and
this is classic theology--

00:57:20.220 --> 00:57:23.970
that God is not more male and
female, that all of maternity

00:57:23.970 --> 00:57:26.820
and all of paternity originate
in the Father and in the Son

00:57:26.820 --> 00:57:28.530
and in the Holy Spirit.

00:57:28.530 --> 00:57:32.940
And the metaphor and
everything else, the imagery,

00:57:32.940 --> 00:57:35.850
is littered through scripture,
and it's in the language.

00:57:35.850 --> 00:57:38.800
But a lot of times it's
been masked over by the fact

00:57:38.800 --> 00:57:45.660
that we haven't allowed that
perspective, because men

00:57:45.660 --> 00:57:47.312
have largely translated
the scriptures.

00:57:47.312 --> 00:57:49.770
Even when you're introduced to
the Holy Spirit in verse two

00:57:49.770 --> 00:57:51.700
in Genesis, it's all feminine.

00:57:51.700 --> 00:57:53.970
Ruach is feminine, the
verbs are feminine,

00:57:53.970 --> 00:57:55.900
pronouns are feminine.

00:57:55.900 --> 00:57:59.520
And the word "mercy" comes from
the same root as the Hebrew

00:57:59.520 --> 00:58:03.360
word for "womb," so every time
you read mercy or compassion,

00:58:03.360 --> 00:58:05.100
you're dealing with womb love.

00:58:05.100 --> 00:58:08.760
When Nicodemus
says, how does a man

00:58:08.760 --> 00:58:13.510
climb into his mother's
womb, that word is used--

00:58:13.510 --> 00:58:17.880
Luke loves that word, talking
about when John the Baptist

00:58:17.880 --> 00:58:19.470
leaped in his mother's womb.

00:58:19.470 --> 00:58:24.030
The word is kopon, and
it's used when John 1:18--

00:58:24.030 --> 00:58:28.230
it says that no one
has seen God face

00:58:28.230 --> 00:58:30.540
to face except the
begotten one who

00:58:30.540 --> 00:58:36.530
has been hidden in the kopon of
the Father, the Father's womb.

00:58:36.530 --> 00:58:40.060
But it's translated "bosom,"
because God the Father can't

00:58:40.060 --> 00:58:41.760
have a womb.

00:58:41.760 --> 00:58:45.570
But again, imagery was never
intended to define God.

00:58:45.570 --> 00:58:47.930
It was intended to help us
understand the character

00:58:47.930 --> 00:58:48.800
and nature of God.

00:58:48.800 --> 00:58:51.390
So God is a burning bush
or a rock or a fortress

00:58:51.390 --> 00:58:53.220
or a strong tower
or a mother bear

00:58:53.220 --> 00:58:56.580
or a woman who loses a coin
or a nursing mother in Isaiah

00:58:56.580 --> 00:59:00.150
or an old man in Ezekiel or
on and on and on and on--

00:59:00.150 --> 00:59:02.160
imagery.

00:59:02.160 --> 00:59:06.000
And imagery is to help
us understand facets

00:59:06.000 --> 00:59:07.950
of the character
and nature of God,

00:59:07.950 --> 00:59:12.660
not to declare the gender
of God or an isolated,

00:59:12.660 --> 00:59:15.240
specific element of the
character and nature of God

00:59:15.240 --> 00:59:17.280
and then make that idolatry.

00:59:17.280 --> 00:59:20.190
So when I wrote
this for my kids,

00:59:20.190 --> 00:59:24.360
I did not want the
revelation of God

00:59:24.360 --> 00:59:28.050
to be inside the
white Western box.

00:59:28.050 --> 00:59:31.920
So the only white Western guy
in the storyline is Mackenzie.

00:59:31.920 --> 00:59:34.170
That's me.

00:59:34.170 --> 00:59:38.040
And I want the character
and nature of God

00:59:38.040 --> 00:59:39.810
to be much bigger than that.

00:59:39.810 --> 00:59:42.400
So the Holy Spirit
is an Asian woman.

00:59:42.400 --> 00:59:46.470
Sophia that comes right out
of Proverbs, Chapter 8--

00:59:46.470 --> 00:59:48.510
"sophia" is the Greek
word for "wisdom"--

00:59:48.510 --> 00:59:53.580
so wisdom personified was played
by Alice Braga from Brazil,

00:59:53.580 --> 00:59:55.350
but is Hispanic.

00:59:55.350 --> 00:59:58.910
And so you've got African,
you've got Hispanic,

00:59:58.910 --> 01:00:00.720
and Jesus, Middle Eastern.

01:00:00.720 --> 01:00:03.390
And so it was
like, no, we've got

01:00:03.390 --> 01:00:05.010
to get outside this white box.

01:00:05.010 --> 01:00:07.440
And all I'm trying to do is
write a story for my kids

01:00:07.440 --> 01:00:13.910
to say, let's not
put God in this box.

01:00:13.910 --> 01:00:18.530
And let that then
begin to help us

01:00:18.530 --> 01:00:22.190
with our understanding of the
character and nature of God.

01:00:22.190 --> 01:00:24.740
So it's a violation
for a lot of us

01:00:24.740 --> 01:00:26.570
because it violates
our paradigms, not

01:00:26.570 --> 01:00:29.270
because it violates scripture.

01:00:29.270 --> 01:00:33.080
It's just that we're used
to thinking a certain way.

01:00:33.080 --> 01:00:36.470
And you know that
understanding has

01:00:36.470 --> 01:00:39.550
to come from changes
of perspective.

01:00:39.550 --> 01:00:40.827
That's how it happens.

01:00:40.827 --> 01:00:42.910
Whether you're dealing
with math or whether you're

01:00:42.910 --> 01:00:48.350
dealing with
psychology or theology,

01:00:48.350 --> 01:00:50.830
you've got to change
your perspective.

01:00:50.830 --> 01:00:53.140
And that's why-- it's in "Eve"--

01:00:53.140 --> 01:00:58.370
I wrote, one good question
is worth a thousand answers,

01:00:58.370 --> 01:01:00.550
because we need to
talk about these things

01:01:00.550 --> 01:01:02.410
and look at our
perspectives and where

01:01:02.410 --> 01:01:03.910
we've got our boxes
that are inside

01:01:03.910 --> 01:01:06.950
our heads that keep us divided
one from another, for one

01:01:06.950 --> 01:01:08.850
thing.

01:01:08.850 --> 01:01:09.350
Good.

01:01:09.350 --> 01:01:10.990
Thank you so much.

01:01:10.990 --> 01:01:13.090
It's been an honor to be here.

01:01:13.090 --> 01:01:16.440
[APPLAUSE]

